5月31日，一位[[欧洲联盟|歐盟]]官員表示小黃瓜很可能在漫長的運輸過程中的某一定點受到汙染<ref name=autogenerated3 />，西班牙官員在之前也表示病源來自西班牙的說法毫無根據；西班牙歐洲事務部長{{le|迪耶戈·羅培茲·加里多|Diego Lopez Garrido|羅培茲}}表示：「你們不能將疫情病源歸咎西班牙。<ref name="bbc2"/>」同日，實驗室測定結果出爐，在受測的四個小黃瓜中有兩個測出大腸桿菌，專家表示較有可能的來源是在德國境內的交叉汙染<ref name="independent1"/>，但測到的大腸桿菌並非病人體中發現的O104菌株。另外兩個小黃瓜中的細菌則尚未被鑑定出。

根據5月31日出版的《[[明镜|明鏡周刊]]》中的一篇文章，將病菌散播到作物上的原因可能包括液態[[有机肥|糞肥]]、被汙染的水與{{Internal link helper/en|西班牙蛞蝓|spanish slug}}，這種蛞蝓在德國境內是長久以來的問題，但在原產地西班牙造成更廣泛且嚴重的問題<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foodpoisonjournal.com/foodborne-illness-outbreaks/could-vector-of-european-e-coli-o104h4-outbreak-be-slugs/ |title=Could Vector of European ''E. coli'' O104:H4 Outbreak be Slugs? : Food Poison Journal : Food Poisoning Lawyer & Attorney : Bill Marler : Marler Clark |publisher=Food Poison Journal |date=2011-05-31 |accessdate=2011-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604205232/http://www.foodpoisonjournal.com/foodborne-illness-outbreaks/could-vector-of-european-e-coli-o104h4-outbreak-be-slugs/ |archive-date=2011-06-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=spiegel31my11>{{cite news|title=The Epidemic Detectives: The Hunt for the Source of Germany's ''E. coli'' Outbreak|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,765777-3,00.html|accessdate=2011-06-04|newspaper=DER SPIEGEL ONLINE|date=2011-05-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110603085715/http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,765777-3,00.html|archive-date=2011-06-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

6月4日，據傳有德國與歐盟官員正在檢察的資料顯示德國北部[[吕贝克|呂貝克]]的一家餐廳可能是這波疫情的源頭，因為有十七個人在這家餐廳用餐後遭到感染<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=128960 |title=E. coli Outbreak Started from German Restaurant - Sofia News Agency |publisher=Novinite.com |date=2011-06-04 |accessdate=2011-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111201220116/http://novinite.com/view_news.php?id=128960 |archive-date=2011-12-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/world/focus-shifts-to-german-restaurant-in-hunt-for-outbreak-source-20110605-1fnb8.html#ixzz1OPYauQbo|title=Focus shifts to German restaurant in hunt for outbreak source|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=2011-06-06|author=Marco Krefting|access-date=2011-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608141302/http://www.smh.com.au/world/focus-shifts-to-german-restaurant-in-hunt-for-outbreak-source-20110605-1fnb8.html#ixzz1OPYauQbo|archive-date=2011-06-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此時，德國各大醫院已經快被感染大腸桿菌的患者占滿<ref>{{cite news|title=Germany 'Struggling To Cope' With E.coli|date=2011-06-05|url=http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/World-News/Ecoli-Outbreak-Germany-Hospitals-Struggle-To-Cope-As-One-Survivor-Speaks-Out-About-The-Problems/Article/201106116005708?lpos=World_News_First_Home_Article_Teaser_Region_3&lid=ARTICLE_16005708_E.coli_Outbreak%3A_Germany_Hospitals_Struggle_To_Cope_As_One_Survivor_Speaks_Out_About_The_Problems|work=SkyNews|access-date=2011-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822080354/https://news.sky.com/?lpos=World_News_First_Home_Article_Teaser_Region_3&lid=ARTICLE_16005708_E.coli_Outbreak:_Germany_Hospitals_Struggle_To_Cope_As_One_Survivor_Speaks_Out_About_The_Problems|archive-date=2019-08-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

