6月5日，下薩克森農業部的一名發言人警告人們不要食用本土產的[[豆芽菜|豆芽菜]]，因為豆芽菜也成了被汙染的作物之一<ref name="guardian1">{{cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jun/05/ecoli-beansprouts-identified-likely-source |title=E coli outbreak: German officials identify bean sprouts as likely source | World news | guardian.co.uk |publisher=Guardian |date= |accessdate=2011-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607210343/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jun/05/ecoli-beansprouts-identified-likely-source |archive-date=2011-06-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。下薩克森境內[[比嫩比特爾|比嫩比特爾]]一處農場生產的豆芽菜疑似為疫情爆發的源頭<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/WORLD/europe/06/05/europe.e.coli/ |title=German-grown sprouts named likely culprit in deadly outbreak - CNN News International Edition |publisher=CNN.com |date=2011-06-05 |accessdate=2011-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110042755/http://www.cnn.com/2011/WORLD/europe/06/05/europe.e.coli/ |archive-date=2012-11-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="connolly1">{{cite web |last=Connolly |first=Allison |url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/e-coli-deaths-at-23-after-another-fatality-as-source-eludes-investigators.html |title=E. Coli Outbreak Kills One More Patient as Source Eludes Investigators |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2008-07-19 |accessdate=2011-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610102237/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/e-coli-deaths-at-23-after-another-fatality-as-source-eludes-investigators.html |archive-date=2011-06-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但6日官員表示這個說法沒有經實驗證實，在疑似感染農場的40個樣本中，有23檢驗結果呈現陰性<ref>{{cite web |author=James Gallagher |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13672161 |title=BBC News - E. coli outbreak: First German sprout tests negative |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2011-06-05 |accessdate=2011-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609034157/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13672161 |archive-date=2011-06-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。6月10日，羅伯特·科赫研究所的負責人{{link-de|萊因哈德·柏格|Reinhard Burger|柏格}}證實豆芽菜為這次疫情的源頭，食用過豆芽菜的人發生出血性[[腹瀉|腹瀉]]（{{lang|en|bloody diarrhea}}）的比率是其他人的九倍<ref>{{cite news|title=Germany says sprouts are most likely source of E.coli|url=http://www.jpost.com/Headlines/Article.aspx?id=224434|accessdate=2011-06-10|newspaper=The Jerusalem Post|date=2011-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023235930/http://www.jpost.com/Headlines/Article.aspx?id=224434|archive-date=2012-10-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13725953|title=German tests link bean sprouts to deadly E. coli|publisher=BBC News|date=2011-06-10|accessdate=2011-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610111934/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13725953|archive-date=2011-06-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]於同日發表的「第13版更新」（{{lang|en|the update 13}}）證實了這項敘述<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euro.who.int/en/what-we-do/health-topics/emergencies/international-health-regulations/news/news/2011/06/ehec-outbreak-update-13|title=EHEC outbreak: update 13|publisher=WHO News|date=2011-06-10|accessdate=2011-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611013457/http://www.euro.who.int/en/what-we-do/health-topics/emergencies/international-health-regulations/news/news/2011/06/ehec-outbreak-update-13|archive-date=2011-06-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

根據德國[[聯邦風險評估研究所|聯邦風險評估研究所]]的國家大腸桿菌實驗室負責人表示，這次爆發的大腸桿菌菌株已在德國境內流傳了十年，對象是人類而非牲畜，食物則疑似遭到人類排泄物的污染<ref>{{cite web|last=MacKenzie|first=Debra|title=Bean sprouts to blame for 'decade-old' E. coli|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn20562-bean-sprouts-to-blame-for-decadeold-e-coli.html|publisher=New Scientist|accessdate=2011-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613103738/http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn20562-bean-sprouts-to-blame-for-decadeold-e-coli.html|archive-date=2011-06-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

